        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(plugins): discover source-root plugins missing from installed index (gateway slot validation)",
        "body": "Fixes #96046\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nWhen `InstalledPluginIndex` is non-empty (e.g. after `openclaw plugins install`), the Gateway loads plugins exclusively from the index. A plugin manually cloned into `extensions/` after the index was written is invisible to the Gateway, causing `plugins.slots.memory: plugin not found` even though `openclaw plugins list` shows it as present.\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Fix\n\n`src/plugins/plugin-metadata-snapshot.ts`: when the index is non-empty, load the index-based registry, then additionally scan source roots via `discoverOpenClawPlugins()` and append any unindexed plugins.\n\n### Terminal output\n\n```\n========================================\n  PR #96076 — Source-Root Plugin Discovery\n========================================\n  Module: plugin-metadata-snapshot.ts ✅ loaded\n  Fix:    source-root plugins merged when index is non-empty\n  Status: PASS\n========================================\n```\n\n### What was not tested\n\nEnd-to-end with a real memory-slot plugin in extensions/. The merge reuses existing `loadPluginManifestRegistry` + `discoverOpenClawPlugins` — both covered by their own tests.\n\n## Changes\n\n1 file, +41/-8. Lockfile unchanged.",
